#. <section class="sutta" id="dn11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn11:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Long Discourses 11"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn11:0.2"
msgid "Kevaṭṭasutta"
msgstr "With Kevaddha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.211"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "dn11:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Nālandā in Pāvārika’s mango grove."

msgctxt "dn11:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho kevaṭṭo "
"gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Kevaddha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:1.4"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā bhagavati "
"abhippasannā."
msgstr "“Sir, this Nāḷandā is successful and prosperous and full of people."

msgctxt "dn11:1.5"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ samādisatu, yo uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karissati;"
msgstr ""
"Sir, please direct a mendicant to perform a demonstration of superhuman "
"psychic power."

msgctxt "dn11:1.6"
msgid "evāyaṃ nāḷandā bhiyyoso mattāya bhagavati abhippasīdissatī”ti."
msgstr "Then Nāḷandā will become even more devoted to the Buddha!”"

msgctxt "dn11:1.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā kevaṭṭaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, The Buddha said:"

msgctxt "dn11:1.8"
msgid "“na kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ desemi:"
msgstr "“Kevaddha, I do not teach the mendicants like this:"

msgctxt "dn11:1.9"
msgid ""
"‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ odātavasanānaṃ uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karothā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Come now, mendicants, perform a demonstration of superhuman psychic power "
"for the white-clothed laypeople.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.212"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:2.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, Kevaddha made the same request,"

msgctxt "dn11:2.2"
msgid "“nāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ dhaṃsemi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:2.3"
msgid "api ca evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:2.4"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā bhagavati "
"abhippasannā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:2.5"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ samādisatu, yo uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karissati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:2.6"
msgid "evāyaṃ nāḷandā bhiyyoso mattāya bhagavati abhippasīdissatī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:2.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā kevaṭṭaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and the Buddha gave the same answer."

msgctxt "dn11:2.8"
msgid "“na kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ desemi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:2.9"
msgid ""
"‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ odātavasanānaṃ uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karothā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:3.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time, Kevaddha made the same request,"

msgctxt "dn11:3.2"
msgid "“nāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ dhaṃsemi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:3.3"
msgid "api ca evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā bhagavati "
"abhippasannā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:3.5"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ samādisatu, yo uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:3.6"
msgid "Evāyaṃ nāḷandā bhiyyoso mattāya bhagavati abhippasīdissatī’”ti."
msgstr "and the Buddha said this:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:3.7"
msgid "1. Iddhipāṭihāriya"
msgstr "1. The Demonstration of Psychic Power"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:3.8"
msgid ""
"“Tīṇi kho imāni, kevaṭṭa, pāṭihāriyāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"paveditāni."
msgstr ""
"“Kevaddha, there are three kinds of demonstration, which I declare having "
"realized them with my own insight."

msgctxt "dn11:3.9"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "dn11:3.10"
msgid "Iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The demonstration of psychic power, the demonstration of revealing, and the "
"demonstration of instruction."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, kevaṭṭa, iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of psychic power?"

msgctxt "dn11:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā "
"bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ tirokuṭṭaṃ "
"tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi "
"ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati "
"seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; "
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃ mahiddhike evaṃ mahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati "
"parimajjati; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying "
"themselves and becoming one again; going unimpeded through a wall, a "
"rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth "
"as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-"
"legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with the hand the "
"sun and moon, so mighty and powerful; controlling the body as far as the "
"Brahmā realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.213"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ aññataro saddho pasanno passati taṃ bhikkhuṃ anekavihitaṃ "
"iddhividhaṃ paccanubhontaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hontaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko "
"hontaṃ; āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ "
"asajjamānaṃ gacchantaṃ seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ "
"karontaṃ seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchantaṃ seyyathāpi "
"pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamantaṃ seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi "
"candimasūriye evaṃ mahiddhike evaṃ mahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasantaṃ "
"parimajjantaṃ yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattentaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then someone with faith and confidence sees that mendicant performing those "
"superhuman feats."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:4.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so saddho pasanno aññatarassa assaddhassa appasannassa āroceti:"
msgstr "They tell someone else who lacks faith and confidence:"

msgctxt "dn11:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, samaṇassa mahiddhikatā "
"mahānubhāvatā."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! The ascetic has such psychic power and might!"

msgctxt "dn11:4.6"
msgid ""
"Amāhaṃ bhikkhuṃ addasaṃ anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhontaṃ—ekopi hutvā "
"bahudhā hontaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hontaṃ … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena "
"vasaṃ vattentan’ti."
msgstr "I saw him myself, performing all these superhuman feats!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:5.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "But the one lacking faith and confidence would say to them:"

msgctxt "dn11:5.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, gandhārī nāma vijjā."
msgstr "‘There’s a spell named Gandhārī."

msgctxt "dn11:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tāya so bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā "
"hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ "
"vattetī’ti."
msgstr "Using that a mendicant can perform such superhuman feats.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:5.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kevaṭṭa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kevaddha? "

msgctxt "dn11:5.5"
msgid "api nu so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyyā”ti?"
msgstr "Wouldn’t someone lacking faith speak like that?”"

msgctxt "dn11:5.6"
msgid "“Vadeyya, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“They would, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn11:5.7"
msgid ""
"“Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, iddhipāṭihāriye ādīnavaṃ sampassamāno "
"iddhipāṭihāriyena aṭṭīyāmi harāyāmi jigucchāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Seeing this drawback in psychic power, I’m horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted by demonstrations of psychic power."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:5.8"
msgid "2. Ādesanāpāṭihāriya"
msgstr "2. The Demonstration of Revealing"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, kevaṭṭa, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of revealing?"

msgctxt "dn11:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisati, "
"cetasikampi ādisati, vitakkitampi ādisati, vicāritampi ādisati:"
msgstr ""
"In one case, someone reveals the mind, mentality, thoughts, and reflections "
"of other beings and individuals:"

msgctxt "dn11:6.3"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is what you’re thinking, such is your thought, and thus is your state "
"of mind.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.214"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:6.4"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ aññataro saddho pasanno passati taṃ bhikkhuṃ parasattānaṃ "
"parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisantaṃ, cetasikampi ādisantaṃ, vitakkitampi "
"ādisantaṃ, vicāritampi ādisantaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then someone with faith and confidence sees that mendicant revealing another "
"person’s thoughts."

msgctxt "dn11:6.5"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:6.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so saddho pasanno aññatarassa assaddhassa appasannassa āroceti:"
msgstr "They tell someone else who lacks faith and confidence:"

msgctxt "dn11:6.7"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, samaṇassa mahiddhikatā "
"mahānubhāvatā."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! The ascetic has such psychic power and might!"

msgctxt "dn11:6.8"
msgid ""
"Amāhaṃ bhikkhuṃ addasaṃ parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisantaṃ, "
"cetasikampi ādisantaṃ, vitakkitampi ādisantaṃ, vicāritampi ādisantaṃ:"
msgstr "I saw him myself, revealing the thoughts of another person!’"

msgctxt "dn11:6.9"
msgid "“evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:7.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "But the one lacking faith and confidence would say to them:"

msgctxt "dn11:7.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, maṇikā nāma vijjā;"
msgstr "‘There’s a spell named Māṇikā."

msgctxt "dn11:7.3"
msgid ""
"tāya so bhikkhu parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisati, cetasikampi "
"ādisati, vitakkitampi ādisati, vicāritampi ādisati:"
msgstr "Using that a mendicant can reveal another person’s thoughts.’"

msgctxt "dn11:7.4"
msgid "“evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:7.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kevaṭṭa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kevaddha? "

msgctxt "dn11:7.6"
msgid "api nu so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyyā”ti?"
msgstr "Wouldn’t someone lacking faith speak like that?”"

msgctxt "dn11:7.7"
msgid "“Vadeyya, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“They would, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn11:7.8"
msgid ""
"“Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, ādesanāpāṭihāriye ādīnavaṃ sampassamāno "
"ādesanāpāṭihāriyena aṭṭīyāmi harāyāmi jigucchāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Seeing this drawback in psychic power, I’m horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted by demonstrations of psychic power."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:7.9"
msgid "3. Anusāsanīpāṭihāriya"
msgstr "3. The Demonstration of Instruction"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:8.1"
msgid "Katamañca, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of instruction?"

msgctxt "dn11:8.2"
msgid "Idha, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu evamanusāsati:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant instructs others like this:"

msgctxt "dn11:8.3"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha, evaṃ manasikarotha, mā evaṃ "
"manasākattha, idaṃ pajahatha, idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Think like this, not like that. Focus your mind like this, not like that. "
"Give up this, and live having achieved that.’"

msgctxt "dn11:8.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the demonstration of instruction."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs9-66"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.215"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:9-66.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, kevaṭṭa, idha tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … "
"pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One arises in the world …"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.2"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti … pe …"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics. …"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.3"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "They enter and remain in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.4"
msgid "Idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "This is called the demonstration of instruction."

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.5"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They enter and remain in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.8"
msgid "Idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "This too is called the demonstration of instruction."

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.9"
msgid "ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti … pe …"
msgstr "They extend and project the mind toward knowledge and vision …"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.10"
msgid "idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "This too is called the demonstration of instruction."

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.11"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti … pe …"
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.12"
msgid "idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr "This too is called the demonstration of instruction."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs67"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:67.1"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, kevaṭṭa, tīṇi pāṭihāriyāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"paveditāni."
msgstr ""
"These, Kevaddha, are the three kinds of demonstration, which I declare "
"having realized them with my own insight."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:67.2"
msgid "4. Bhūtanirodhesakabhikkhuvatthu"
msgstr "4. On the Mendicant In Search of the Cessation of Being"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:67.3"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, kevaṭṭa, imasmiññeva bhikkhusaṅghe aññatarassa bhikkhuno evaṃ "
"cetaso parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Once it so happened, Kevaddha, that a mendicant in this very Saṅgha had the "
"following thought:"

msgctxt "dn11:67.4"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
"pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, "
"namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs68"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:68.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu tathārūpaṃ samādhiṃ samāpajji, yathāsamāhite "
"citte devayāniyo maggo pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then that mendicant attained a state of immersion such that a path to the "
"gods appeared."

msgctxt "dn11:68.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena cātumahārājikā devā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā cātumahārājike deve etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then he approached the Gods of the Four Great Kings and said:"

msgctxt "dn11:68.3"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left "
"over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.216"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:68.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, cātumahārājikā devā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When he said this, those gods said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:68.5"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma:"
msgstr "‘Mendicant, we too do not know this."

msgctxt "dn11:68.6"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:68.7"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bhikkhu, cattāro mahārājāno amhehi abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā "
"ca."
msgstr "But the Four Great Kings are our superiors."

msgctxt "dn11:68.8"
msgid "Te kho etaṃ jāneyyuṃ:"
msgstr "They might know.’"

msgctxt "dn11:68.9"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs69"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:69.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena cattāro mahārājāno tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā cattāro mahārāje etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then he approached the Four Great Kings and asked the same question."

msgctxt "dn11:69.2"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:69.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, cattāro mahārājāno taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "But they also said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:69.4"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma:"
msgstr "‘Mendicant, we too do not know this."

msgctxt "dn11:69.5"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu, "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:69.6"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bhikkhu, tāvatiṃsā nāma devā amhehi abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā "
"ca."
msgstr "But the gods of the Thirty-Three …"

msgctxt "dn11:69.7"
msgid "Te kho etaṃ jāneyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:69.8"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs70"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:70.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena tāvatiṃsā devā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā tāvatiṃse deve etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:70.2"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:70.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, tāvatiṃsā devā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:70.4"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:70.5"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:70.6"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bhikkhu, sakko nāma devānamindo amhehi abhikkantataro ca "
"paṇītataro ca."
msgstr "Sakka, the lord of gods …"

msgctxt "dn11:70.7"
msgid "So kho etaṃ jāneyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:70.8"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs71"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.217"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:71.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena sakko devānamindo tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:71.2"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:71.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, sakko devānamindo taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:71.4"
msgid "‘ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:71.5"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs72"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:72.1"
msgid "Atthi kho, bhikkhu, yāmā nāma devā … pe …"
msgstr "the gods of Yāmā …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs73"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:73.1"
msgid "suyāmo nāma devaputto …"
msgstr "the god named Suyāma …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs74"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:74.1"
msgid "tusitā nāma devā …"
msgstr "the Joyful gods …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs75"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:75.1"
msgid "santussito nāma devaputto …"
msgstr "the god named Santussita …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs76"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:76.1"
msgid "nimmānaratī nāma devā …"
msgstr "the gods who delight in creation …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs77"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:77.1"
msgid "sunimmito nāma devaputto …"
msgstr "the god named Sunimmita …"

msgctxt "dn11:77.2"
msgid "paranimmitavasavattī nāma devā …"
msgstr "the gods who control the creation of others …"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs78"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:78.1"
msgid "vasavattī nāma devaputto amhehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca."
msgstr "the god named Vasavattī …"

msgctxt "dn11:78.2"
msgid "So kho etaṃ jāneyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:78.3"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs79"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.220"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:79.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena vasavattī devaputto tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā vasavattiṃ devaputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:79.2"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:79.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, vasavattī devaputto taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:79.4"
msgid "‘ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:79.5"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:79.6"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bhikkhu, brahmakāyikā nāma devā amhehi abhikkantatarā ca "
"paṇītatarā ca."
msgstr "the gods of Brahmā’s Group."

msgctxt "dn11:79.7"
msgid "Te kho etaṃ jāneyyuṃ:"
msgstr "They might know.’"

msgctxt "dn11:79.8"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs80"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:80.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu tathārūpaṃ samādhiṃ samāpajji, yathāsamāhite "
"citte brahmayāniyo maggo pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then that mendicant attained a state of immersion such that a path to Brahmā "
"appeared."

msgctxt "dn11:80.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena brahmakāyikā devā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā brahmakāyike deve etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then he approached those gods and said:"

msgctxt "dn11:80.3"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left "
"over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’"

msgctxt "dn11:80.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, brahmakāyikā devā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "But they also said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:80.5"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma:"
msgstr "‘Mendicant, we too do not know this."

msgctxt "dn11:80.6"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn11:80.7"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso "
"vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānaṃ amhehi "
"abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca."
msgstr ""
"But there is Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the "
"Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, "
"the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been "
"born and those yet to be born. He is our superior."

msgctxt "dn11:80.8"
msgid "So kho etaṃ jāneyya:"
msgstr "He might know.’"

msgctxt "dn11:80.9"
msgid ""
"“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu "
"āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.221"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:80.10"
msgid "‘Kahaṃ panāvuso, etarahi so mahābrahmā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But reverends, where is that Brahmā now?’"

msgctxt "dn11:80.11"
msgid ""
"‘Mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma, yattha vā brahmā yena vā brahmā yahiṃ vā "
"brahmā;"
msgstr "‘We also don’t know where he is or what way he lies."

msgctxt "dn11:80.12"
msgid ""
"api ca, bhikkhu, yathā nimittā dissanti, āloko sañjāyati, obhāso "
"pātubhavati, brahmā pātubhavissati, brahmuno hetaṃ pubbanimittaṃ "
"pātubhāvāya, yadidaṃ āloko sañjāyati, obhāso pātubhavatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But by the signs that are seen—light arising and radiance appearing—we know "
"that Brahmā will appear. For this is the precursor for the appearance of "
"Brahmā, namely light arising and radiance appearing.’"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs81"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:81.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, mahābrahmā nacirasseva pāturahosi."
msgstr "Not long afterwards, the Great Brahmā appeared."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:81.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena so mahābrahmā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then that mendicant approached the Great Brahmā and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:81.3"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left "
"over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’"

msgctxt "dn11:81.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, so mahābrahmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Great Brahmā said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:81.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahamasmi, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso "
"vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I am Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal "
"Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, "
"the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and "
"those yet to be born.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs82"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:82.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, that mendicant said to the Great Brahmā:"

msgctxt "dn11:82.2"
msgid "‘na khohaṃ taṃ, āvuso, evaṃ pucchāmi:"
msgstr "‘Reverend, I am not asking you whether you are"

msgctxt "dn11:82.3"
msgid ""
"“tvamasi brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī "
"issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, "
"the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the "
"Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those "
"yet to be born."

msgctxt "dn11:82.4"
msgid "Evañca kho ahaṃ taṃ, āvuso, pucchāmi:"
msgstr "I am asking"

msgctxt "dn11:82.5"
msgid ""
"“kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti?"
msgstr "where these four primary elements cease without anything left over.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:82.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so, kevaṭṭa, mahābrahmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, the Great Brahmā said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:82.7"
msgid ""
"‘ahamasmi, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso "
"vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I am Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal "
"Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, "
"the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and "
"those yet to be born.’"

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs83"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:83.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time, that mendicant said to the Great Brahmā:"

msgctxt "dn11:83.2"
msgid "‘na khohaṃ taṃ, āvuso, evaṃ pucchāmi:"
msgstr "‘Reverend, I am not asking you whether you are"

msgctxt "dn11:83.3"
msgid ""
"“tvamasi brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī "
"issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, "
"the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the "
"Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those "
"yet to be born."

msgctxt "dn11:83.4"
msgid "Evañca kho ahaṃ taṃ, āvuso, pucchāmi:"
msgstr "I am asking"

msgctxt "dn11:83.5"
msgid ""
"“kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti?"
msgstr "where these four primary elements cease without anything left over.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.222"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:83.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, mahābrahmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ bāhāyaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ "
"apanetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Great Brahmā took that mendicant by the arm, led him off to one "
"side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:83.7"
msgid ""
"‘ime kho maṃ, bhikkhu, brahmakāyikā devā evaṃ jānanti, “natthi kiñci "
"brahmuno aññātaṃ, natthi kiñci brahmuno adiṭṭhaṃ, natthi kiñci brahmuno "
"aviditaṃ, natthi kiñci brahmuno asacchikatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Mendicant, these gods think that there is nothing at all that I don’t know "
"and see and understand and realize."

msgctxt "dn11:83.8"
msgid "Tasmāhaṃ tesaṃ sammukhā na byākāsiṃ."
msgstr "That’s why I didn’t answer in front of them."

msgctxt "dn11:83.9"
msgid ""
"Ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāmi yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā "
"nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātūti."
msgstr ""
"But I too do not know where these four primary elements cease with nothing "
"left over."

msgctxt "dn11:83.10"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhu, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ taṃ "
"bhagavantaṃ atidhāvitvā bahiddhā pariyeṭṭhiṃ āpajjasi imassa pañhassa "
"veyyākaraṇāya."
msgstr ""
"Therefore, mendicant, the misdeed is yours alone, the mistake is yours "
"alone, in that you passed over the Buddha and searched elsewhere for an "
"answer to this question."

msgctxt "dn11:83.11"
msgid ""
"Gaccha tvaṃ, bhikkhu, tameva bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā imaṃ pañhaṃ puccha, "
"yathā ca te bhagavā byākaroti, tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Mendicant, go to the Buddha and ask him this question. You should remember "
"it in line with his answer.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs84"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:84.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā "
"bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva brahmaloke "
"antarahito mama purato pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then that mendicant, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract "
"their arm, vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of me."

msgctxt "dn11:84.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi, ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho, kevaṭṭa, so bhikkhu maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then he bowed, sat down to one side, and said to me:"

msgctxt "dn11:84.3"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, bhante, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, "
"namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn11:84.4"
msgid "4.1. Tīradassisakuṇupamā"
msgstr "4.1. The Simile of the Land-Spotting Bird"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs85"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.223"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ—"
msgstr "When he said this, I said to him:"

msgctxt "dn11:85.2"
msgid ""
"bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhu, sāmuddikā vāṇijā tīradassiṃ sakuṇaṃ gahetvā nāvāya "
"samuddaṃ ajjhogāhanti."
msgstr ""
"‘Once upon a time, mendicant, some sea-merchants set sail for the ocean "
"deeps, taking with them a land-spotting bird."

msgctxt "dn11:85.3"
msgid "Te atīradakkhiniyā nāvāya tīradassiṃ sakuṇaṃ muñcanti."
msgstr "When their ship was out of sight of land, they released the bird."

msgctxt "dn11:85.4"
msgid ""
"So gacchateva puratthimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati "
"pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ disaṃ, gacchati "
"anudisaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It flew right away to the east, the west, the north, the south, upwards, and "
"in-between."

#. VAR: tathāgatakova → tathā pakkantova (s1) | tathāpakkanto va (s2, s3)
msgctxt "dn11:85.5"
msgid "Sace so samantā tīraṃ passati, tathāgatakova hoti."
msgstr "If it saw land on any side, it went there and stayed."

msgctxt "dn11:85.6"
msgid "Sace pana so samantā tīraṃ na passati, tameva nāvaṃ paccāgacchati."
msgstr "But if it saw no land on any side it returned to the ship."

msgctxt "dn11:85.7"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, yato yāva brahmalokā pariyesamāno imassa pañhassa "
"veyyākaraṇaṃ nājjhagā, atha mamaññeva santike paccāgato."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, after failing to get an answer to this question even after "
"searching as far as the Brahmā realm, you’ve returned to me."

msgctxt "dn11:85.8"
msgid "Na kho eso, bhikkhu, pañho evaṃ pucchitabbo:"
msgstr "Mendicant, this is not how the question should be asked:"

msgctxt "dn11:85.9"
msgid ""
"‘kattha nu kho, bhante, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, "
"seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, "
"namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.10"
msgid "Evañca kho eso, bhikkhu, pañho pucchitabbo:"
msgstr "This is how the question should be asked:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.11"
msgid "‘Kattha āpo ca pathavī,"
msgstr "“Where do water and earth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.12"
msgid "tejo vāyo na gādhati;"
msgstr "fire and air find no footing;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.13"
msgid "Kattha dīghañca rassañca,"
msgstr "where do long and short,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.14"
msgid "aṇuṃ thūlaṃ subhāsubhaṃ;"
msgstr "fine and coarse, beautiful and ugly;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.15"
msgid "Kattha nāmañca rūpañca,"
msgstr "where does name and form"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.16"
msgid "asesaṃ uparujjhatī’ti."
msgstr "cease with nothing left over?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.17"
msgid "Tatra veyyākaraṇaṃ bhavati:"
msgstr "And the answer to that is:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.18"
msgid "‘Viññāṇaṃ anidassanaṃ,"
msgstr "“Consciousness that’s invisible,"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/whose-consciousness-is-invisible-infinite-and-all-radiant/4098
#. <br>
#. VAR: sabbatopabhaṃ → \
msgctxt "dn11:85.19"
msgid "anantaṃ sabbatopabhaṃ;"
msgstr "infinite, radiant all round."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.20"
msgid "Ettha āpo ca pathavī,"
msgstr "Here’s where water and earth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.21"
msgid "tejo vāyo na gādhati."
msgstr "fire and air find no footing;"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.22"
msgid "Ettha dīghañca rassañca,"
msgstr "here’s where long and short,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.23"
msgid "aṇuṃ thūlaṃ subhāsubhaṃ;"
msgstr "fine and coarse, beautiful and ugly;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.24"
msgid "Ettha nāmañca rūpañca,"
msgstr "here’s where name and form"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.25"
msgid "asesaṃ uparujjhati;"
msgstr "cease with nothing left over—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.26"
msgid "Viññāṇassa nirodhena,"
msgstr "with the cessation of consciousness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.27"
msgid "etthetaṃ uparujjhatī’”ti."
msgstr "that’s where this ceases.”’”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "dn11:85.28"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn11:85.29"
msgid "Attamano kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr ""
"Satisfied, the householder Kevaddha was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn11:85.30"
msgid "Kevaṭṭasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
